{"title_page": "Geetha Arts", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} \n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{advert|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox company  \n| name = Geetha Arts\n| logo = Geetha Arts.jpg\n| logo_size = 250px\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]   \n| parent = \n| owner = [[Allu Aravind]]\n| foundation = [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]] in 1972\n| location_city = [[Hyderabad, Telangana]]\n| location_country = India\n| key_people = [[Allu Aravind]]<br/>[[Allu Arjun]]<br/>Allu Venkatesh <br/>[[Allu Sirish]]\n| subsid =\n<div>\n* GA2 Pictures\n</div>\n |industry = [[Entertainment]]\n| products = [[Films]]\n| revenue =\n| operating_income =\n| homepage = [http://www.geethaarts.com Geetha Arts]\n}}\n\n'''Geetha Arts''' ([[Telugu language|Telugu]]: \u0c17\u0c40\u0c24\u0c3e \u0c06\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c4d\u0c38\u0c4d, Formerly known as '''Geetha Art Productions''' ([[Telugu language|Telugu]]: \u0c17\u0c40\u0c24\u0c3e \u0c06\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c4a\u0c21\u0c15\u0c4d\u0c37\u0c28\u0c4d\u0c38\u0c4d), '''Geetha Cine Enterprises''' ([[Telugu language|Telugu]]: \u0c17\u0c40\u0c24\u0c3e \u0c38\u0c3f\u0c28\u0c40 \u0c0e\u0c02\u0c1f\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c2a\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c48\u0c1c\u0c46\u0c38\u0c4d), '''Geetha Creative Arts''' ([[Telugu language|Telugu]]: \u0c17\u0c40\u0c24\u0c3e \u0c15\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c3f\u0c2f\u0c47\u0c1f\u0c3f\u0c35\u0c4d \u0c06\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c4d\u0c38\u0c4d)) is an [[Cinema of India|Indian film]] production and distribution company established in 1972 by [[Allu Aravind]], brother-in-law of [[Chiranjeevi]]. The company is based in [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]] and has produced around 40 films in [[Telugu language|Telugu]], [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Kannada]]  and [[Hindi]] languages.\n\nGeetha Arts though came to be known for its big-budget blockbusters, the company marked its beginning by producing a small-budget movie ''[[Bantrotu Bharya|Banthrotu Bharya]]''  in 1974. The company delivered several successful projects from the beginning, the film ''[[Vijetha]]'' , a family drama starring [[Chiranjeevi]]  set the trend of blockbusters for Geetha Arts. Since then, Geetha Arts has made movies mostly featuring superstars such as [[Chiranjeevi]], [[Rajinikanth]], [[V Ravichandran]], [[Aamir Khan]], [[Pawan Kalyan]], [[Allu Arjun]], [[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]], [[Nani (actor)| Nani]], [[Ram Charan]], and [[Vijay Deverakonda]].\n\nAfter consolidating the film production business, Geetha Arts expanded its presence into film distribution, exhibition and digital content. In the highly fragmented and unorganized industry, Geetha Arts is one of the few players that has streamlined its business and evolve into an integrated film conglomerate.\n\n== Aha ==\n{{main|Aha (streaming service)}} \nAllu Aravind in association with MyHome Group owner started [[Over-the-top media service|OTT]] named \"Aha\" which went live on Feb 08,2020.\n\n== GA2 Pictures ==\n'''GA2 Pictures''' is [[Independent movie|indie]] production arm of Geetha Arts on which they produce small and medium budgeted movies and managed by Bunny Vas.\n{{Infobox company\n| name = GA2 Pictures\n| logo = \n| type = [[Subsidiary]]\n| parent =\n| owner = [[Geetha Arts]] \n| foundation = [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]] in 2014\n| location_city = [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]] \n| location_country = India\n| key_people = Bunny Vas\n| subsid =\n| industry = [[Entertainment]]\n| products = [[Films]]\n| revenue =\n| operating_income =\n}}\n=== Film Production ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Year\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Film\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Language\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Director\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Cast\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Notes\n|-\n|| 2015 ||''[[Bale Bale Magadivoy]]''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|[[Maruthi Dasari]]||[[Nani (actor)|Nani]] and [[Lavanya Tripathi]]|| Co-production with [[UV Creations]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-03-03/Bhale-Bhale-Magadivoy--a-Family-entertainer-134975|title=Bhale Bhale Magadivoy , a Family entertainer|work=The Hans India|date=3 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|| 2016 ||''[[Sundaranga Jaana]]''\n|[[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n|[[Ramesh Aravind]]||[[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]], [[Shanvi Srivastava]] || Co-production with [[Rockline Venkatesh|Rockline Entertainments Pvt Lmt]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |2018 ||''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|[[Parasuram (director)|Parasuram]]||[[Vijay Devarakonda]] and [[Rashmika Mandanna]]||\n|-\n|''[[Taxiwaala]]''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|[[Rahul Sankrityan]]||[[Vijay Deverakonda]], [[Priyanka Jawalkar]] and [[Malavika Nair (Indian actress)|Malavika Nair]]||Co-production with [[UV Creations]]\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Prati Roju Pandage]]''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|[[Maruthi Dasari]]\n|[[Sai Dharam Tej]] and [[Rashi Khanna]]\n|Co-production with [[UV Creations]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2020 ||''[[Most Eligible Bachelor (2020 film)|Most Eligible Bachelor]]''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|[[Bhaskar (director)|Bhaskar]]||[[Akhil Akkineni]] and [[Pooja Hegde]]||\n|-\n|''Chavu Kaburu Challaga''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Koushik Pegallapati||Karthikeya||\n|-\n|''18 Pages''\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|[[Palnati Surya Pratap]]\n|[[Nikhil Siddharth]]\n|Co-production with [[Sukumar Writings]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Film production==\n\nAs a production house, Geetha Arts has been gaining popularity in the last few years. ''Jalsa'', a Telugu film starring Pawan Kalyan grossed $10 million at the box office. It was the biggest hit of 2008 and the second highest grosser amongst Telugu films. Their next \u2013 ''Ghajini'', a Bollywood movie starring Aamir Khan grossed over $45 million at box office, making it the highest grossing Indian film. The smashing blockbuster ''[[Magadheera]]'', a big-budget swords and sandal epic that grossed $25 million at the box office. The movie was not only the highest-grossing Telugu film ever, but the highest grossing Indian movie in 2009. The movie is a crown jewel in Telugu cinema for two reasons. ''Magadheera'' unlocked the box office potential of Telugu films by doing numbers that only a few big-budget Bollywood blockbusters can match. Secondly, with its Hollywoodesque grandeur, special effects and action episodes it showed the Telugu cinema can churn out films of international standards.\n\n===Geetha Arts===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Year\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Film\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Language\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Director\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#b0c4de;\"| Notes\n\n|-\n|| 1974 || ''[[Bantrotu Bharya]]'' || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] || [[Dasari Narayana Rao]] || Produced as '''Geetha Art Productions'''\n|-\n|| 1975 || ''Devude Digivaste'' ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| Dasari Narayana Rao || Produced as '''Geetha Art Productions'''\n|-\n|| 1979 || ''Maavullo Mahasivudu'' ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]||Raja Chandra || Produced as '''Geetha Cine Enterprises'''\n|-\n|| 1982 || ''[[Yamakinkarudu]]'' ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| Raj Bharat || Produced as '''Geetha Creative Arts'''\n|-\n|| 1984 || ''[[Hero (1984 film)|Hero]]'' || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] || [[Vijaya Bapineedu]] ||\n|-\n|| 1985 || ''[[Vijetha]]'' ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| [[A. Kodandarami Reddy]] || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1987 || ''[[Aradhana (1987 film)|Aradhana]]'' ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| [[P. Bharathiraja|Bharathiraja]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[Pasivadi Pranam]]'' ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| [[A. Kodandarami Reddy]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1989 || ''[[A